  "page": "Snakewood (forest)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Vale.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"The Vale and the location of the snakewood\"><img alt=\"The Vale and the location of the snakewood\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/29/The_Vale.png/350px-The_Vale.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/29/The_Vale.png/525px-The_Vale.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/29/The_Vale.png/700px-The_Vale.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 27.8%; left: 50%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -8px; top: -8px; width: 15px; font-size: 15px;\"><img alt=\"The Vale and the location of the snakewood\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/15px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Snakewood\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/23px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/30px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size: 100%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; top:-0.15em; left: -3em; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\"><b>Snakewood</b></span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\"><a href=\"/index.php/The_Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Vale\">The Vale</a> and the location of the snakewood\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><table>\n\n<tbody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>snakewood</b> is a forest in the north of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lynderly\" title=\"House Lynderly\">House Lynderly</a> have the title \"Lord of the Snakewood\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and rule from their castle, which is also called <a href=\"/index.php/Snakewood\" title=\"Snakewood\">Snakewood</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i> depicts a forest in the vicinity of Heart's Home, although it does not extend as far as the castles of Snakewood, Coldwater, or Strongsong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiaf_westeros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiaf_westeros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Snakewood_(forest)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Appendix\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Appendix\">Appendix</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The castle of Snakewood was called \"Sunkenwood\" in earlier works.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtloiaf_westeros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiaf_westeros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.